1
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:09,630
EVERY MASCULINE GENDER OF
THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA SHALL

2
00:00:09,710 --> 00:00:11,090
FAITHFULLY PERFORM
MANDATORY MILITARY SERVICE,

3
00:00:11,170 --> 00:00:14,090
AS PRESCRIBED BY THE CONSTITUTION
OF THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA AND THIS ACT

4
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:17,930
ARTICLE 3 OF THE MILITARY SERVICE ACT

5
00:00:18,970 --> 00:00:20,390
[child crying]

6
00:00:20,470 --> 00:00:23,640
10 YEARS AGO

7
00:00:25,940 --> 00:00:28,440
-[man] Have you lost it?
-[slaps]

8
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:33,360
You think you're better than me
because you have some money?

9
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:35,320
-Gosh, you're unbelievable.
-[girl sobs]

10
00:00:36,030 --> 00:00:39,490
[man] Fuck it.
It's like I'm living with a vulture.

11
00:00:41,540 --> 00:00:43,710
[girl cries]

12
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:48,500
Your sister's crying, you punk.

13
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,250
[girl sobs]

14
00:00:51,340 --> 00:00:52,460
[door bangs]

15
00:00:54,670 --> 00:00:57,550
[heavy breathing]

16
00:01:00,220 --> 00:01:02,770
[girl sobbing continues]

17
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:06,310
EPISODE 3: THAT WOMAN

18
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,150
[theme music plays]

19
00:01:29,380 --> 00:01:33,920
♪ Since I've been dreaming for too long ♪

20
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:41,260
♪ I can't find the reasons to move on ♪

21
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:46,350
♪ Wake up to reality ♪

22
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:50,270
♪ Realize we're getting old ♪

23
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:53,270
♪ All our goals ♪

24
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:57,240
♪ Are breaking down ♪

25
00:02:04,450 --> 00:02:06,870
[man on PA]
As a soldier of the 103rd division,

26
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:09,420
let's start the day brightly.

27
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:13,920
[Jun-ho] Private Cho, it's okay.
It doesn't need to be that nice.

28
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,170
Jun-ho-kun, I'm using fire
to polish your boots.

29
00:02:16,260 --> 00:02:19,180
Seniors do this for juniors
who go on leave.

30
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:21,890
[Suk-bong] It's all done.

31
00:02:23,390 --> 00:02:24,720
Sit down.

32
00:02:27,350 --> 00:02:28,600
Thank you, sir.

33
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:30,100
I'm jealous of you, Jun-ho-kun.

34
00:02:30,190 --> 00:02:32,060
I've never been rewarded
an extra leave before.

35
00:02:35,150 --> 00:02:37,400
No, you don't need to feel sorry.

36
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:39,240
Have fun. Enjoy your time outside.

37
00:02:40,110 --> 00:02:43,740
But by any chance,
if you have some extra time,

38
00:02:44,450 --> 00:02:45,830
can you get me this?

39
00:02:45,910 --> 00:02:47,200
I want this color.

40
00:02:48,330 --> 00:02:49,830
I use it to draw comics.

41
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:54,340
Sure. Okay, sir.

42
00:02:54,420 --> 00:02:55,920
Thank you.
[chuckles]

43
00:02:56,800 --> 00:03:00,880
[Ji-seop] How is this carbon?
It's obviously aluminum.

44
00:03:01,380 --> 00:03:04,010
I'll call you back. Just wait. Bye.

45
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:07,310
This punk…

46
00:03:09,060 --> 00:03:11,060
Ho-yeong. Jun-woo.

47
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:13,560
Private An Jun-ho, sir.

48
00:03:13,650 --> 00:03:15,360
Corporal Han Ho-yeol, sir.

49
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:17,320
You guys did great.

50
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:20,860
I'm sure all those deserters
want to be left alone,

51
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:23,820
but our D.P. just goes
and catches them all.

52
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:26,080
It's very rewarding, isn't it? Great work.

53
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:29,080
-They found him on the street.
-Still, I'd say they're talented.

54
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:31,620
It's only the first half,
and you already caught seven.

55
00:03:31,710 --> 00:03:32,830
[Ji-seop] Impressive.

56
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:35,920
Let's catch ten this year, okay?

57
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,550
-Sergeant Park, are you okay with that?
-Well, sure. Yes.

58
00:03:38,630 --> 00:03:41,130
Have fun on your leave.
Don't get yourselves in trouble.

59
00:03:41,220 --> 00:03:42,680
Ho-yeong and Jun-woo.

60
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:45,050
Private An Jun-ho, sir.

61
00:03:45,140 --> 00:03:46,720
Corporal Han Ho-yeol, sir.

62
00:03:50,770 --> 00:03:53,230
You're free to have fun on your leave,

63
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:55,690
but sleep with your phones
in your underwear.

64
00:03:55,770 --> 00:03:58,570
What if I don't wear underwear? Sir?

65
00:04:00,570 --> 00:04:02,070
I bet he does that on purpose.

66
00:04:03,530 --> 00:04:05,030
Jun-woo, let's go.

67
00:04:05,110 --> 00:04:06,780
Private An Jun-ho, sir.

68
00:04:07,370 --> 00:04:09,040
[Ho-yeol]
Just be casual when we're outside.

69
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:09,950
[Jun-ho] Okay, sir.

70
00:04:10,620 --> 00:04:12,370
[light music plays]

71
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:14,540
[Ho-yeol] Instant noodles
without endocrine disruptors

72
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:16,540
as requested by Private An
from Bongcheon-dong.

73
00:04:16,630 --> 00:04:18,800
It's almost done. Coming right up.

74
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,960
[slurps]

75
00:04:22,170 --> 00:04:24,430
-Do you have any brothers?
-[slurps]

76
00:04:25,050 --> 00:04:27,800
-I have a younger sibling.
-[muffled] Mm. A younger sister?

77
00:04:27,890 --> 00:04:29,140
She's not pretty.

78
00:04:29,220 --> 00:04:30,140
I didn't ask.

79
00:04:31,890 --> 00:04:33,310
Are your parents doing well?

80
00:04:33,390 --> 00:04:34,690
I guess they're okay.

81
00:04:36,270 --> 00:04:39,520
Why are you giving such insincere answers
to your senior?

82
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:42,150
You told me to be casual outside.

83
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:44,990
Right.

84
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:46,740
[whispers] What a smart-ass.

85
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:48,490
[slurps]

86
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:52,790
Did you start boxing when you were little?
Did your parents make you do it?

87
00:04:52,870 --> 00:04:55,420
I learned it so I could avoid
getting beaten up by my dad.

88
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:58,000
Okay.

89
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,920
[Jun-ho slurps]

90
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:02,960
Why did our parents give birth to us?

91
00:05:03,050 --> 00:05:04,220
[Jun-ho slurps]

92
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:06,090
[Ho-yeol] I never asked to be born.

93
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:09,850
[music playing on radio]

94
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:11,220
I know, right?

95
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:13,980
-[slurps]
-[dog barking tone from cell phone]

96
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:18,440
My gosh. Beom-gu always calls
at the worst times.

97
00:05:19,650 --> 00:05:21,940
Corporal Han Ho-yeol on the phone, sir.

98
00:05:22,690 --> 00:05:25,360
[groans]
But we're on leave. That's…

99
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:30,740
Busan?

100
00:05:36,330 --> 00:05:37,170
[grunts]

101
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,590
[shouts]

102
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,590
I called the D.P. soldiers as you asked.

103
00:05:45,670 --> 00:05:47,470
They'll be heading to Busan right away.

104
00:05:48,260 --> 00:05:50,930
-[in English] Set point.
-[soldier in Hangul] That's right, sir.

105
00:05:51,010 --> 00:05:52,850
[Beom-gu sighs]

106
00:05:52,930 --> 00:05:54,640
This may be out of line,

107
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:57,390
but we shouldn't bother them
when they're on leave.

108
00:05:57,980 --> 00:06:00,230
We shouldn't involve ourselves
with deserters from other…

109
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:02,940
[groans]

110
00:06:03,020 --> 00:06:04,280
I didn't see you there.

111
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,940
[exhales]

112
00:06:06,030 --> 00:06:07,360
[Ji-seop] I'm sorry.

113
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:09,700
[sucks teeth]
Nice reflexes.

114
00:06:09,780 --> 00:06:12,030
The grip on this racket's a bit weird.

115
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:14,160
[soldier]
I'm sorry, sir. I'll get you a new one.

116
00:06:14,950 --> 00:06:16,500
Do you have something to report?

117
00:06:17,410 --> 00:06:19,790
No, sir. Have a good day.

118
00:06:19,870 --> 00:06:20,750
[Ji-seop] Sure.

119
00:06:23,090 --> 00:06:25,170
[whispers]
He keeps nudging me the wrong way.

120
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:28,090
[chuckles]

121
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:33,550
[upbeat music plays]

122
00:06:38,390 --> 00:06:39,980
♪ The day of the sea ♪

123
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:42,940
Jun-ho, let's have beef ribs
after we eat this.

124
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:45,650
Is it really okay to do this?

125
00:06:45,730 --> 00:06:48,440
Yes, this is a cooperative investigation.

126
00:06:48,530 --> 00:06:50,820
We're just helping the D.P.
from another unit.

127
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:52,740
After we're done helping,

128
00:06:52,820 --> 00:06:53,910
this…

129
00:06:54,910 --> 00:06:57,580
♪ Beef ribs ♪

130
00:06:57,660 --> 00:07:00,250
-That's what we'll be having.
-Right.

131
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:01,670
SAMJIN FISH CAKES

132
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:03,880
[Ho-yeol] He's handsome.

133
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:05,210
I hear he's a good fighter.

134
00:07:06,590 --> 00:07:08,800
There are two types of deserters.

135
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:12,300
Guys who are scary because you don't know
what they'll end up doing.

136
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:15,600
And guys who are just plain scary.

137
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:18,930
Choi Jun-mok was the former,
and he's the latter.

138
00:07:19,020 --> 00:07:20,020
Ugh.

139
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:21,640
What do you mean?

140
00:07:21,730 --> 00:07:23,020
[Ho-yeol] They're tough.

141
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:26,270
Some even used to be in gangs.

142
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:28,780
You could even get stabbed. Ugh.

143
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:31,110
Don't worry.

144
00:07:31,990 --> 00:07:34,240
We're just here to help.

145
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:39,500
[upbeat music playing continues]

146
00:07:49,130 --> 00:07:50,260
[in English] Hi, Busan.

147
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:52,840
[Ho-yeol in Hangul] I love Busan.

148
00:07:53,430 --> 00:07:54,720
[imitates seagull caws]

149
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:58,180
[upbeat music playing]

150
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:04,150
[Ho-yeol] Wah…

151
00:08:04,230 --> 00:08:07,020
[in English] Nice view. Nice view.

152
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:10,610
[in Hangul] Hello.

153
00:08:10,690 --> 00:08:11,570
Hello.

154
00:08:11,650 --> 00:08:14,360
Right. You must be from Gangwon-do.

155
00:08:14,950 --> 00:08:17,070
Yes, would you like some potatoes?

156
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,700
Give him one.

157
00:08:18,780 --> 00:08:21,120
We're out of potatoes.

158
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,830
[whispers]
I guess we forgot to bring them.

159
00:08:22,910 --> 00:08:23,790
Nice to meet you.

160
00:08:23,870 --> 00:08:25,290
Yes, hello. We're…

161
00:08:25,370 --> 00:08:28,210
I'm Kim Gyu, the head of the D.P.
at the Capital Defense Command.

162
00:08:29,210 --> 00:08:32,800
Yes, nice to meet you.
[nervous chuckle]

163
00:08:33,590 --> 00:08:35,930
[indistinct chatter]

164
00:08:36,010 --> 00:08:38,930
You couldn't possibly afford to come here
with the money you get.

165
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:43,980
But you're wearing a shiny suit
and you're dressed like a penguin.

166
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:47,100
You must use your mother's credit card.

167
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:50,110
I love my mother's credit card.

168
00:08:50,190 --> 00:08:51,070
[in English] A penguin…

169
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:56,860
[in Hangul]
I heard you're here to assist us.

170
00:08:56,950 --> 00:08:58,070
"Assist"?

171
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:02,200
We're here to help because you've been
struggling to catch this guy.

172
00:09:02,830 --> 00:09:04,330
Ah…

173
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:06,330
[whispers] Is there a problem?

174
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:07,920
I'm fine.

175
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:12,460
Okay.
[chuckles]

176
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:13,670
Seong-gon.

177
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:17,720
We traced his whereabouts
and tried to guess where he went.

178
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:20,640
Take a look. This is where
Jeong Hyeon-min's father lives.

179
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:23,310
And this is where his girlfriend lives.

180
00:09:23,390 --> 00:09:25,310
They're busy,

181
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:27,440
so just keep it short.

182
00:09:27,940 --> 00:09:29,020
I'm sorry, sir.

183
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,690
You just need to go here.

184
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:34,820
We'll go to his father's place instead.

185
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,660
You're okay with that, right?

186
00:09:37,740 --> 00:09:39,320
Okay, sure. Go ahead.

187
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,490
[Gyu] We'll be off.

188
00:09:44,950 --> 00:09:46,330
Thank you in advance.

189
00:09:47,830 --> 00:09:50,080
-Let's go.
-[Seong-gon] Thank you in advance.

190
00:09:50,170 --> 00:09:53,800
[tranquil music playing in the restaurant]

191
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:54,920
This is annoying.

192
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:58,130
They must use good beans.

193
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,840
I love the acidity.

194
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:02,680
Why did you act that way earlier?

195
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:05,350
Well, you see, I don't like Choco Pies.

196
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:08,480
But I really craved them
when I was in boot camp.

197
00:10:08,980 --> 00:10:11,900
So I went to church and got one.

198
00:10:11,980 --> 00:10:14,190
But instead of eating it,
I kept it in my locker.

199
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,610
Why do you think I did that?

200
00:10:16,860 --> 00:10:19,360
So I could save it
until the fifth week of training

201
00:10:19,450 --> 00:10:21,950
and have it once it was all over.

202
00:10:22,030 --> 00:10:24,040
But there's this jerk who stole it.

203
00:10:25,410 --> 00:10:26,620
What would you have done?

204
00:10:28,540 --> 00:10:29,670
I would have killed him.

205
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:32,790
Kim Gyu was that asshole.
But he doesn't remember.

206
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:34,500
He's one sick son of a bitch.

207
00:10:34,590 --> 00:10:35,880
Hold it in. Stay put.

208
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:38,800
This is no longer a joke.
We're going to catch Jeong Hyeon-min.

209
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:42,720
His girlfriend's place
is obviously not important.

210
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,470
Unit 307, Haeundae-gu 432-7, Busan.

211
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:48,100
It's Jeong Hyeon-min's father's address.
I memorized it.

212
00:10:48,850 --> 00:10:51,020
I'm impressed you caught that.

213
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:52,810
Let's go get him before they do.

214
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:54,020
[doorbell dings]

215
00:10:55,270 --> 00:10:56,650
[Hyeon-min]
What the hell are you doing, idiot?

216
00:10:56,730 --> 00:10:58,860
-Gosh, you dumbass.
-[doorbell dings]

217
00:10:58,940 --> 00:11:01,240
Let's go, damn it. Let's do this. Come on.

218
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,330
-My gosh, fuck this.
-[dinging continues]

219
00:11:04,410 --> 00:11:06,160
[man talking on video game]

220
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,870
They're coming from behind, asshole!

221
00:11:07,950 --> 00:11:10,250
-He fucking shot me from behind.
-[doorbell dings]

222
00:11:10,330 --> 00:11:12,170
Open the door already, for fuck's sake!

223
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:14,000
This is fucking annoying.

224
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:15,880
-Where's the old man gone off to?
-[door opens]

225
00:11:16,590 --> 00:11:20,050
-Hello, we're from the church nearby.
-[sighs]

226
00:11:20,130 --> 00:11:22,050
Do you have time for a short chat?

227
00:11:22,130 --> 00:11:24,600
I'll fucking kill you!

228
00:11:25,180 --> 00:11:26,720
Just go. Stop bothering me.

229
00:11:26,810 --> 00:11:27,770
Can't you spare…

230
00:11:29,310 --> 00:11:30,390
Fuck.

231
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:31,520
-[toilet flushes]
-[door opens]

232
00:11:32,730 --> 00:11:33,900
Was someone here?

233
00:11:33,980 --> 00:11:35,270
[Hyeon-min sighs]

234
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:38,190
I fucking told you to answer the door.

235
00:11:38,780 --> 00:11:40,400
-[grunts]
-[metal clanks]

236
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,280
Hyeon-min.

237
00:11:45,370 --> 00:11:47,620
Shouldn't you go back to your unit now?

238
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:51,080
You could really end up
ruining your life at this rate.

239
00:11:52,210 --> 00:11:54,330
[scoffs]
Fuck.

240
00:11:57,420 --> 00:11:58,960
How much worse can things get?

241
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:02,380
Don't you know
who ruined my life in the first place?

242
00:12:04,970 --> 00:12:06,050
Don't you?

243
00:12:07,350 --> 00:12:08,390
[glass shatters]

244
00:12:08,470 --> 00:12:10,430
Hyeon-min! You're bleeding!

245
00:12:13,270 --> 00:12:14,980
If you have no money, just shut up.

246
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:17,940
I don't care if you're my dad.
I'll fuck you up.

247
00:12:18,020 --> 00:12:19,070
[doorbell dings]

248
00:12:19,150 --> 00:12:20,530
I'll go check who it is.

249
00:12:20,610 --> 00:12:22,860
Those fucking Jesus freaks!

250
00:12:22,950 --> 00:12:24,360
What do you fucking want?

251
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,490
Jeong Hyeon-min?

252
00:12:26,990 --> 00:12:28,080
[Ho-yeol] It really is him.

253
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:31,830
-Fuck…
-[all grunt]

254
00:12:31,910 --> 00:12:33,710
[Hyeon-min] Get lost, you shits.

255
00:12:33,790 --> 00:12:34,710
[grumbles]

256
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:36,750
